items.title: First victim of the deadly Kazakhstan plane crash is buried in Azerbaijan
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
One of the victims of a deadly plane crash in Kazakhstan was buried on Friday. Ramazan Filiev, 26, was one of 38 people killed when Azerbaijan Airlines' Embraer 190 was diverted for reasons still unclear on Wednesday and crashed while making an attempt to land in Aktau in Kazakhstan.

items.title: Holes seen in the tail of the plane crashed in Kazakhstan
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
An online video showed holes in the tail section of the Azerbaijani plane that crashed Thursday in Kazakhstan and killed 38 people. Aviation experts said that Russian air defense fire was likely responsible for the crash of Azerbaijan Airlines' Embraer 190 that was en route from Baku to the Russian city of Grozny in the North Caucasus.

items.title: Children become victims of unprecedented violence in Chile
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
The killing of a 10-year-old girl in Chile shocked the South American country in January 2024. Agustina Pascale became one of the first public faces of an unprecedented wave of killings that is on track to leave a record number of minors as victims of criminal gangs this year—whether recruited or killed in the crossfire. By mid-November, a total of 48 children had been killed by firearms, six more than were recorded in all of 2023, officials said.  
(AP Video by Mauricio Cuevas)
